AWKA – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship candidate in the November 6, 2021 governorship election and winner of this year’s ‘Anambra Man of The Year ‘ Mr. Valentine Chineto Ozigbo, has dedicated his award to his father who he said shaped his life and those of his siblings. His father, Chief Andrew Nwafor Ozigbo, passed away on January 3 at the age of 92. Ozigbo said: “Papa laid the foundation for what I have become. Without him, my life would have taken a whole different path, and I am grateful for the many sacrifices he and my mother made to ensure that my six siblings and I received a noble and enlightened upbringing.” Late Ogeh Was Intelligent Professional – Okowa Friends Celebrate Olusemire As Customs’ New Assist Comptroller… He said he was deeply touched by the honour of being chosen by Ndi Anambra and profoundly grateful for the great year that 2021 was. According to him, “God did many astonishing things in 2021, and He used many beautiful humans to extend His grace and love to him.” Ozigbo also dedicated the award to the youths of Anambra State, who he said have continued to be his supporters. He said he believed that the youths hold the key that unlocks the bright promise of Anambra’s future and from what he has seen heard, and experienced in the past two years, particularly during the campaigns, empowering the youth is the sure and fastest path to realising our true potentials as a people.